fix: codebase audit — input conventions, broken overlay URL, stale docs

Changes:

- js/aria-player.js : copyOverlayUrl() had a regex that never matched the actual
  URL structure (views/aria-player.html). The replace silently no-oped, so the
  copied URL still pointed to aria-player.html instead of aria-overlay.html.
  Fixed to replace(/aria-player\.html.*$/, 'aria-overlay.html').
  renderSkillsEditor(), renderSpecialsEditor(), and renderInventoryEditor() used
  type="number" inputs — replaced with type="text" inputmode="numeric" per
  project convention.

- js/aria-gm.js : Updated stale comment on the players Map (was "playerId ->"
  since the charId migration). Replaced type="number" in addAmfAttack(),
  removeAmfAttack() re-render loop, and renderMonsters() monster attack inputs.

- views/aria-player.html : Replaced all type="number" inputs (free-roll
  threshold, stat fields FOR/DEX/END/INT/CHA/PV, armure value) with
  type="text" inputmode="numeric" + oninput filter.

- views/aria-gm.html : Same for monster creation form (PV, armure, stat fields)
  and GM roll threshold inputs (free roll + monster roll).

- CLAUDE.md : Corrected potionRecipes field name from `chance` to
  `successChance` (2 occurrences — character structure and potion-grant payload).
